    dc:description "FIGURES 75–81. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., photos. 75–80. Female. 75. Dorsal idiosoma; 76. Opisthonotal shield; 77. Ventral idiosoma; 78. Incision of ventri-anal shield; 79. Sternal and genital regions; 80. Sternal shields; 81. Male, ventral idiosoma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601546/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601530>
    dc:description "FIGURE 48. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., female. Dorsal idiosoma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601530/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601542>
    dc:description "FIGURES 66–69. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., SEM photos, female. 66. Dorsal idiosoma; 67–69. Ventral idiosoma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601542/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601532>
    dc:description "FIGURES 49–50. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., female. 49. Ventral idiosoma; 50.Different variants of genital shields." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601532/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601534>
    dc:description "FIGURES 51–55. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., female. 51. Chelicera; 52. Epistome; 53. Gnathosoma with corniculi and internal malae; 54. Hypostome; 55. Gnathosoma, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601534/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601544>
    dc:description "FIGURES 70–74. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., SEM photos. 70–73. Female.70. Sternal and genital regions; 71. Peritrematal shield with peritrema; 72. Peritrema; 73. Gnathosoma; 74. Male, ventral idiosoma." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2601544/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2601536>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–59. Halozercon kazachok sp. n., male. 56. Ventral idiosoma; 57. First and second sternal shields with genital opening; 58. Genital sclerites; 59. Chelicera." ;
